## Quality Criteria (Self-Check)

Before marking bundle complete, verify:

- [ ] **Built from Cold snapshot** (snapshot ID format verified, no Hot paths)
- [ ] **All links/anchors resolve** across formats (MD/HTML/EPUB/PDF)
- [ ] **No orphan sections** (every section reachable from TOC or crosslinks)
- [ ] **Terminals marked** clearly (story endpoints obvious to reader)
- [ ] **Codex coverage** sufficient for high-frequency terms; See-also links resolve
- [ ] **Alt text present** for all non-decorative images; descriptive (not technique talk)
- [ ] **Descriptive link text** (no "click here" or "see here")
- [ ] **Heading structure** valid (no skipped levels, meaningful titles)
- [ ] **Options correctly reflected** (art/audio/translations match front matter claims)
- [ ] **Translations flagged** `complete`/`incomplete` with coverage percentages
- [ ] **Front matter stamped** with snapshot ID, options, accessibility, coverage, limitations
- [ ] **View Log updated** with TUs merged (player-safe titles), known limitations
- [ ] **Assembly Notes documented** (harmless normalizations transparent)
- [ ] **Hooks proposed** for upstream fixes (broken links, ambiguous labels, spoilers)
- [ ] **No internals on surfaces** (no codewords, gate logic, seeds/models, technique talk)
- [ ] **Integrity + Presentation + Accessibility self-check: PASS**

---

## Safety Rails

- **ABORT if mixing Hot and Cold:** Views are snapshots, not work-in-progress
- **NEVER rewrite text to pass bars:** Propose hooks to owners; re-bind after upstream fixes
- **NEVER surface internals:** Codewords, gate logic, seeds/models, DAW plugins, technique talk
- **ALWAYS disclose limitations:** Incomplete translations, deferred assets, known gaps
- **Respect register/terminology:** Ask Style/Translator before changing labels
- **Repro notes off-surface:** Determinism/asset logs live in build notes, NOT front matter
- **Harmless normalizations only:** Heading case, anchor format—changing meaning requires owner approval

